subject: Implements Redfish PCIeSlots schema in bmcweb
commitMessage:
Implements Redfish PCIeSlots schema in bmcweb

This commit implements Redfish PCIeSlots schema on bmcweb.
The PCIeSlots schema is a set of PCIe slot information for
a Redfish implementation. It is used to get the PCIeType,
SlotType, Lanes, HotPluggable, and so on of the PCIE slot.

Looking for an association with the name "chassis" to determine
the PCIeSlot to chassis.
I pushed a commit to add these associations to the design document:
https://gerrit.openbmc-project.xyz/c/openbmc/docs/+/44263/2

Reference: https://redfish.dmtf.org/schemas/v1/PCIeSlots.v1_4_1.yaml

Tested: Validator passes.
1、Get PCIe slots
curl -k -H "X-Auth-Token: $token" -X GET
https://${bmc}/redfish/v1/Chassis/chassis/PCIeSlots
{
  "@odata.id": "/redfish/v1/Chassis/chassis/PCIeSlots",
  "@odata.type": "#PCIeSlots.v1_4_1.PCIeSlots",
  "Id": "PCIeSlots",
  "Name": "PCIe Slot Information",
  "Slots": [
    {
      "HotPluggable": false,
      "Lanes": 16,
      "PCIeType": "Gen1",
      "SlotType": "FullLength"
    },
    {
      "HotPluggable": false,
      "Lanes": 16,
      "PCIeType": "Gen2",
      "SlotType": "OEM"
    }
  ]
}

2、No PCIeSlots
curl -k -H "X-Auth-Token: $token" -X GET
https://${bmc}/redfish/v1/Chassis/chassis/PCIeSlots
{
  "@odata.id": "/redfish/v1/Chassis/chassis/PCIeSlots",
  "@odata.type": "#PCIeSlots.v1_4_1.PCIeSlots",
  "Id": "PCIeSlots",
  "Name": "PCIe Slot Information",
  "Slots": []
}

3、Bad chassis ID return 404
curl -k -H "X-Auth-Token: $token" -X GET
https://${bmc}/redfish/v1/Chassis/badChassisID/PCIeSlots
{
  "error": {
    "@Message.ExtendedInfo": [
      {
        "@odata.type": "#Message.v1_1_1.Message",
        "Message": "The requested resource of type
        	 Chassis named badChassisID was not found.",
        "MessageArgs": [
          "Chassis",
          "badChassisID"
        ],
        "MessageId": "Base.1.8.1.ResourceNotFound",
        "MessageSeverity": "Critical",
        "Resolution": "Provide a valid resource identifier
                       and resubmit the request."
      }
    ],
    "code": "Base.1.8.1.ResourceNotFound",
    "message": "The requested resource of type Chassis
                named badChassisID was not found."
  }
}

Signed-off-by: Chicago Duan <duanzhijia01@inspur.com>
Change-Id: I11e1bf94b3865986cbd580293ea906fe96067912
